  "doc_id": "584",
  "text": "While clearly important, p14 is nonessential for production of mature infectious virions. Thus, the protein does not perform an obligate function in virion maturation and/or assembly. Rather, it appears to affect the overall efficiency of the virion assembly process, either directly or indirectly. Using IEM and Western blotting with anti-9GL antiserum, we were unable to detect p14 in virions. This suggests a nonstructural function for the protein in efficient virion assembly. As is the case with scERV1 in yeast and with other ERV1 homologues, our data suggest that p14 may be a low-abundance protein in infected cells (24, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
